# MSME Digital Lending Sandbox — Java & JavaFX Conversion Plan

## Project Background

The current **MSME Digital Lending Sandbox** is a Loan Origination System (LOS) built with:

| Layer | Current Stack |
|---|---|
| Backend API | FastAPI (Python 3.x) |
| Admin Frontend | React (Vite + JSX) |
| Borrower App | Flutter (Dart) |
| Database | PostgreSQL via SQLAlchemy ORM |

This document details how to **re-implement the same system** as a **Java and JavaFX Application** targeting the same functional scope (Borrower applications, Admin review, Risk Engine, reporting).

---

## New Java & JavaFX Tech Stack

Instead of a separate Web and Mobile application, the new architecture will use **JavaFX** to build robust Desktop client applications, powered by a **Java Spring Boot** backend. 

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Language | **Java 21** (or Java 17 LTS) |
| IDE | **IntelliJ IDEA** or Eclipse |
| Client UI Framework | **JavaFX** (with FXML and SceneBuilder) |
| Backend API Framework| **Spring Boot** (Spring Web, Spring Security) |
| Database Connectivity| **Spring Data JPA (Hibernate)** / JDBC |
| Database | **PostgreSQL** or **MySQL** |
| Build Tool | **Maven** or Gradle |

*(Note: If you prefer a simpler 2-tier architecture without an API, JavaFX can connect directly to the database using JDBC or Hibernate. However, a 3-tier Spring Boot architecture provides better security and matches the current FastAPI setup.)*

---

## Architecture Translation

| Current System (Python/Flutter/React) | New System (Java/JavaFX/Spring) | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **FastAPI Backend** | **Spring Boot REST API** | Handles all business logic, routing, and database access. |
| **Flutter Borrower App** | **JavaFX Borrower Desktop App** | A JavaFX desktop client where borrowers can apply for loans, calculate EMIs, and view history. |
| **React Admin Panel** | **JavaFX Admin Desktop App** | A dashboard built in JavaFX for administrators to review loans, change statuses, and view charts. |
| **SQLAlchemy ORM** | **Spring Data JPA (Hibernate)** | Manages database connectivity, ORM mapping, and CRUD operations. |
| **JWT Auth (python-jose)** | **Spring Security + JWT** | Secures endpoints and authenticates users on login. |

